headlines.description: — Jarrett Allen said the Cleveland Cavaliers are out to change how they're perceived around the NBA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavaliers hold off Hornets' 4th-quarter rally, win 113-110

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Indiana Pacers coach Rick Carlisle spent the first two weeks plugging holes.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers snap 4-game losing streak, rout Spurs 131-118

headlines.description: — Seth Curry stepped up in Joel Embiid’s absence, scoring 23 points — including several key buckets late — to lead the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers to a 113-103 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Seth Curry's 23 helps short-handed 76ers over Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 26 points, Clint Capela had 16 points and 12 rebounds, and the Atlanta Hawks beat the Washington Wizards 118-111 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young, Capela help Hawks end Wizards' 3-game winning streak

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 37 points and the Chicago Bulls rallied from a 19-point, second-half deficit on Monday night to beat the Boston Celtics 128-114 and improve to 6-1 for the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 37 as Bulls beat Celtics 128-114 to reach 6-1

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The Toronto Raptors were midway through a dominant third quarter when Svi Mykhailiuk's basket gave them the lead for good.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anunoby has career-best 36, Raptors beat Knicks 113-104

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 26 points, eight assists and seven rebounds, Tyus Jones added 17 points and the Memphis Grizzlies defeated the Denver Nuggets 106-97 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores 26 to lead Grizzlies past Nuggets 106-97

headlines.description: — Cole Anthony scored a season-high 31 points and Wendell Carter Jr. chipped in 15 points and 14 rebounds as the Orlando Magic came from behind to beat the Minnesota Timberwolves 115-97 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony's 31 leads Magic to 115-97 win against Timberwolves

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — With his team in a shooting slump to start the season and 3 of 21 from 3-point range during the first half Monday night, Los Angeles Clippers coach Ty Lue kept his message simple at halftime.
headlines.shortLinkText: George scores 32, Clippers rally late in 4th to beat Thunder
